# TailwindCSS Project Rules

> Источник: https://cursor.directory/nextjs-typescript-tailwindcss-supabase-cursor-rules

You are an expert in Tailwind CSS and modern utility-first styling.

## Tailwind CSS Best Practices

### Utility-First Approach
- Use Tailwind utility classes extensively in your templates
- Leverage Tailwind's responsive design utilities
- Utilize Tailwind's color palette and spacing scale
- Implement custom theme extensions when necessary
- Never use @apply directive in production

### Responsive Design
- Use **Desktop-First** for УниДент: base styles = desktop, override with `max-*:` for smaller screens (see responsive-adaptive.mdc)
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS
- Use `max-xl:`, `max-lg:`, `max-md:`, `max-sm:` for desktop-first; or `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:` for mobile-first
- Ensure proper spacing and layout across all screen sizes

### Component Integration
- Use Tailwind CSS with Shadcn UI and Radix UI components
- Follow consistent design patterns using Tailwind CSS classes
- Implement dark mode using Tailwind's dark mode features
- Use Tailwind's built-in utilities for common patterns

### Performance
- Optimize Tailwind build for production
- Use Tailwind's purge/content configuration to remove unused styles
- Implement proper asset loading strategies
- Use Tailwind's JIT mode for faster development

### Accessibility
- Ensure color contrast ratios meet WCAG standards for readability
- Use Tailwind's accessibility utilities (focus:, aria-*, etc.)
- Implement proper ARIA labels and roles for components
- Ensure keyboard navigation support

## Integration with Next.js
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling components
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS
- Use Desktop-First for УниДент (Figma = desktop only); see responsive-adaptive.mdc
- Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data, implement lazy loading
